records.addlTxt: Status conference on December 15, 2022 at 09:30 am.

(10:09 AM case called.) Defendant John J. Molnar in court, in custody. Attorney Roger M Hillestad in court for John J. Molnar. Prosecuting attorney Tiffany M. Winter in court for the State of Wisconsin.
State in compliance with victim notification requirements. 
Defendant waives reading of Information and enters Not Guilty pleas to all counts, which the Court accepts.
Attorney Hillestad advises the defendant is currently awaiting revocation in other non-related matters and is hoping for a global resolution.
Attorney Hillestad requests to schedule a status conference about 30-60 days out.
Status Conference scheduled for December 15, 2022 at 9:30 am (1/2 hour) in person.

2:19 PM Defendant John J. Molnar in court, in custody.  Attorney Roger M Hillestad in court for John J. Molnar.  Attorney Andrew James Gunderson in court for State of Wisconsin. This is the time and date set for a Preliminary Hearing. Parties are ready to proceed.

State calls Officer Jimmy Vang, ECPD to the stand; sworn and testifies. Witness identifies the Defendant on the record. Defense stipulates to Defendant's identity. 
Cross examination by Defense. 
Witness steps down.

Court finds probable cause and binds the matter over. Case referred to Br. 3 for scheduling an arraignment.

Preliminary hearing scheduled for August 30, 2022 at 02:00 pm.
The Defendant is eligible for State Public Defender Services. Despite best efforts, the State Public Defender Office has not yet secured representation for this Defendant.

(Case called at 2:29 PM) Defendant John Molnar appears in person in custody without counsel. ADA Andrew Gunderson appears in person for the State of Wisconsin. 
Court advises the Defendant of charges and potential penalties. Court reads Probable Cause portion of the criminal complaint to the Defendant. Court advises the Defendant of his right to an attorney. State requests $2,000 cash bond- recites failures to appear. Court orders $2,000 cash bond with various conditions. Defendant indicates he is seeking counsel. 
Court finds probable cause to continue time limits.
